WEBVTT

00:01.876 --> 00:03.461
-Hey.
ADAM: Hey, whoa.

00:03.628 --> 00:04.837
Snazzy getup, Aud.

00:05.005 --> 00:06.797
Thank you. I've decided
to get back into running.

00:06.964 --> 00:10.843
And buying outfits that make you look
like you're from the future.

00:11.010 --> 00:15.098
I am from the future.
Guess what? I'm single.

00:15.598 --> 00:18.351
Fine. I'll be dating
a bunch of sexy robots.

00:22.688 --> 00:26.692
It's a good thing that you, uh,
ripped the tags off that new outfit.

00:26.859 --> 00:29.779
Wouldn't wanna be able
to return it after you give up.

00:30.321 --> 00:31.697
I'm not gonna give up.

00:31.864 --> 00:36.202
I'm as committed to running
as you are to clogging your arteries.

00:36.911 --> 00:38.329
I doubt it.

00:40.706 --> 00:41.749
Well....

00:41.916 --> 00:44.419
Well, if you'll excuse me,
I have to, uh, get to the office.

00:44.585 --> 00:48.256
Now that you're not working,
I have to try.

00:51.342 --> 00:54.011
He's so stressed out about money,
but he's too manly to admit it.

00:54.179 --> 00:56.264
Jennifer is the same way.

00:56.431 --> 00:58.933
Why don't they know
it's okay to open up?

01:00.268 --> 01:03.688
Dopey, Bashful, Busty.

01:04.605 --> 01:06.982
Sir, isn't that the same outfit
you were wearing--

01:07.150 --> 01:09.652
When you opened
for the Doobie Brothers?

01:11.904 --> 01:14.157
I was going to say last night.

01:14.324 --> 01:16.826
It is indeed the same outfit
I, uh, wore last night...

01:16.992 --> 01:19.120
...because I had an away game.

01:19.829 --> 01:20.871
Is this the end of it...

01:21.038 --> 01:23.874
...or should I prepare for yet another
woman storming into your office...

01:24.041 --> 01:27.295
...to deliver a Who's Afraid
Of Virginia Woolf? style tirade?

01:28.296 --> 01:29.547
[ADAM CHUCKLES]

01:29.714 --> 01:34.260
Virginia Woolf?
No, Timmy, it's the big bad wolf.

01:36.971 --> 01:39.515
No, Mr. Rhodes, I was actually....

01:40.225 --> 01:41.809
Thank you.

01:42.643 --> 01:44.812
Anyway, Heather's great.
She's sweet and funny.

01:44.979 --> 01:48.358
We laugh. We talk.
We kissed on the mouth.

01:48.816 --> 01:51.611
-Sounds like you really like this girl.
-I do, and it's not just physical.

01:51.777 --> 01:52.945
I like hanging out with her.

01:53.113 --> 01:56.199
-So how'd you guys leave things?
-I don't know. I snuck out.

01:56.824 --> 01:59.660
-Why?
-Habit, I guess.

01:59.827 --> 02:04.582
Open eyes, back of chick's head,
not my apartment, skedoodle.

02:04.749 --> 02:05.750
[IMITATES WHOOSH]

02:05.916 --> 02:06.917
[AUDREY CHUCKLES]

02:07.084 --> 02:09.003
-You should go back.
-Can you go back, though?

02:09.170 --> 02:11.422
Can you unskedoodle?

02:11.589 --> 02:14.300
-Yeah, if you really like her, why not?
-Yeah, I do.

02:14.467 --> 02:15.468
-I'm going back.
-Good.

02:15.635 --> 02:18.679
Oh. It's like running over a bunny
with your car...

02:18.846 --> 02:21.557
...and then getting out
and shooting it.

02:23.518 --> 02:24.852
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S
"HOW MANY WAYS" PLAYING]

02:25.395 --> 02:28.356
♪ How many ways
To say I love you ♪

02:30.941 --> 02:34.111
♪ How many ways
To say that I'm not scared ♪

02:35.321 --> 02:40.075
♪ With you by my side
There is no denying ♪

02:40.243 --> 02:42.453
♪ I can't wait for me and you ♪♪

02:48.125 --> 02:50.127
[♪♪♪]

02:52.129 --> 02:54.340
DAN: Oh, hey, Jeff.
-Hey, Dan, what's up?

02:54.507 --> 02:57.385
-I'm collecting for Janet's baby gift.
-Didn't I already kick in for that?

02:57.552 --> 02:59.595
No, that was
Janet's baby shower gift.

02:59.804 --> 03:01.055
Ah.

03:02.139 --> 03:05.518
I'm surprised I wasn't asked to kick in
for the booze her husband used...

03:05.685 --> 03:07.270
...when he knocked her up.

03:09.689 --> 03:13.359
I mean, why don't you just
bend me over, Janet?

03:15.069 --> 03:17.655
Yeah, maybe don't sign the card.

03:18.239 --> 03:21.617
Oh, oh, and it's Todd's birthday today.
I'm collecting for a cake.

03:21.784 --> 03:25.663
Oh, a cake? Is Todd turning nine?

03:25.871 --> 03:27.290
Here.

03:28.165 --> 03:31.126
Here's a little extra. Why don't you
get him a bounce house too?

03:31.877 --> 03:33.879
[♪♪♪]

03:34.630 --> 03:35.923
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

03:37.508 --> 03:39.719
-Hey.
-Russell, where did you go?

03:39.885 --> 03:43.681
I ran out to get you this. It's like you.
Soft, delicious, and low in fat.

03:43.848 --> 03:45.308
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

03:45.975 --> 03:47.977
So I thought
we could hang out this morning.

03:48.143 --> 03:50.145
Oh, that sounds great. I'd love to.

03:50.313 --> 03:52.565
Wait. I'm getting a text.

03:52.732 --> 03:56.527
Oh, shoot.
I've gotta run into the office.

03:56.694 --> 03:59.113
Oh, I understand.
Wanna get lunch?

03:59.280 --> 04:02.533
I wish I could but I'm stacked up
all day with work stuff.

04:02.700 --> 04:06.036
Oh, message received. Dinner?

04:06.203 --> 04:08.205
-Dinner. Heh, it's a plan.
-Okay.

04:08.373 --> 04:11.334
Wait, I have a weekly work meeting
Wednesday nights.

04:11.501 --> 04:12.585
Well, tonight's Thursday.

04:12.752 --> 04:15.421
Ah, Wednesday and Thursday
are my two worst nights.

04:15.588 --> 04:17.757
I've got work functions
on both of them.

04:17.923 --> 04:19.925
You couldn't have had one last night,
we were together.

04:20.092 --> 04:21.093
It was before that.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.470
Anyway, I better go get ready...

04:22.637 --> 04:25.931
...but I have your number, so I'll call
if things get a little less hectic, okay?

04:26.098 --> 04:28.183
She said she's gonna call me.

04:29.394 --> 04:32.730
Hm. So that's what you took away
from all that?

04:33.439 --> 04:36.359
It's not what I took away.
That's what she said.
She's gonna call me.

04:36.526 --> 04:37.818
I see.

04:37.985 --> 04:42.657
Wow. Um, the thing is,
I'm not quite sure how to put this--

04:42.823 --> 04:45.951
I think what Timmy's
trying to say is....

04:46.786 --> 04:49.414
Congratulations, man.
It sounds like she's really into you.

04:49.580 --> 04:51.165
-That's right. Yeah.
-Yeah.

04:51.332 --> 04:52.750
[RUSSELL SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

04:53.501 --> 04:55.503
[♪♪♪]

04:56.837 --> 05:00.174
Yo, Jeff. The raffle tickets are in.

05:00.341 --> 05:01.967
Time to pay the piper.

05:02.134 --> 05:05.012
Which raffle tickets? What piper?

05:05.471 --> 05:07.640
My lodge's charity raffle,
remember?

05:07.807 --> 05:10.518
Fifty bucks a ticket,
grand prize is a Volkswagen Jetta.

05:10.685 --> 05:13.979
-You said you'd buy a ticket.
-Oh, I've changed my mind.

05:15.856 --> 05:19.985
-So you don't wanna buy one?
-No, detective, I don't.

05:20.445 --> 05:23.155
Come on. Everyone else
in the office bought a ticket.

05:23.323 --> 05:26.075
What is this, socialist Canada?

05:26.909 --> 05:30.746
-Actually, I don't think Canada is--
-Look, look, I have just....

05:30.913 --> 05:34.124
I've had enough of having
everyone's hands in my pocket.

05:34.291 --> 05:37.294
In fact, you know what? That's it.

05:42.508 --> 05:45.052
Excuse me.
Can I have everyone's attention?

05:45.803 --> 05:50.766
I am sick of you parasites
asking me to contribute, donate...

05:50.933 --> 05:54.395
...or kick in to,
uh, every charity raffle...

05:54.562 --> 05:57.898
...or stupid event
in your pathetic lives. I'm out!

06:02.027 --> 06:04.154
Happy birthday, Todd.

06:05.573 --> 06:07.575
[♪♪♪]

06:08.576 --> 06:10.578
Really?
Right in the middle of Todd's party?

06:10.745 --> 06:11.954
Yeah, I just snapped.

06:12.497 --> 06:13.623
Everyone was pretty shocked.

06:13.789 --> 06:16.792
It didn't help when I took
the first piece of cake.

06:18.043 --> 06:21.506
Hey, Jeff, Audrey thinks you're really
stressed out about money.

06:21.672 --> 06:23.298
Why don't you talk to her about it?

06:23.466 --> 06:24.509
That's not how I do things.

06:24.675 --> 06:26.677
I, uh, believe that a man
provides for his woman...

06:26.844 --> 06:29.054
...without ever complaining
or showing stress...

06:29.221 --> 06:32.266
...all the while
silently resenting her for it.

06:32.433 --> 06:36.020
Cool, cool.
Okay, well, I should take off.

06:38.188 --> 06:39.273
-Hey.
-Hey.

06:39.440 --> 06:40.733
Hey.

06:40.900 --> 06:43.235
I just got back from running
with Kate. Guess what.

06:43.611 --> 06:46.447
I hate this game.
You never appreciate my guesses.

06:47.364 --> 06:51.076
She's doing a 10K charity fun run,
and I decided to sign up.

06:51.243 --> 06:54.079
Is it topless?
Because that would be a real fun run.

06:55.873 --> 06:58.918
"Are you sure you can't do better?"
All my friends said.

06:59.084 --> 07:00.753
"Yes, I'm sure."

07:02.296 --> 07:04.507
All right, well,
good for you and Kate.

07:04.674 --> 07:06.801
Tomorrow I'm gonna bring
this pledge sheet to your office...

07:06.967 --> 07:09.053
...and get your coworkers
to donate money.

07:12.890 --> 07:15.768
Coworkers?
I don't think that's, uh, a good idea.

07:16.268 --> 07:17.853
Why? I'm raising money
for a good cause.

07:18.020 --> 07:21.023
Come on. Look, if they were gonna
find a cure for this disease...

07:21.190 --> 07:23.859
...uh, wouldn't they have
found one already?

07:25.194 --> 07:26.446
It's for an animal shelter.

07:28.280 --> 07:29.824
Still.

07:30.700 --> 07:33.911
Heh, heh,
why the sudden anti-charity stance?

07:34.078 --> 07:35.788
Look, I....

07:35.955 --> 07:40.710
I just don't think that the people
in my office are very generous.

07:41.836 --> 07:43.921
Well, it can't hurt to ask.

07:45.840 --> 07:49.510
Fine. If you're gonna
be stubborn about this...

07:50.553 --> 07:52.262
...I'll take care of it.

07:57.309 --> 07:59.311
[♪♪♪]

08:00.312 --> 08:01.313
[RUSSELL GROANS]

08:01.481 --> 08:03.357
I can't believe Heather
hasn't called me yet.

08:03.524 --> 08:04.692
I know.

08:04.859 --> 08:07.528
Maybe my phone's broken.
Give me a call.

08:07.695 --> 08:09.321
[TIMMY SIGHS]

08:10.948 --> 08:12.825
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

08:12.992 --> 08:14.619
Heather?

08:15.703 --> 08:18.288
Babe? Hello?

08:18.455 --> 08:20.082
No, sir, it's me.

08:20.249 --> 08:23.418
Well, quit tying up the line.
She might be trying to call me.

08:24.253 --> 08:27.131
Man, she must be super busy.

08:27.297 --> 08:31.176
Busy sanding off her fingerprints
and changing her identity.

08:32.553 --> 08:34.346
Oh, hey, dude,
why don't you just call her?

08:34.514 --> 08:36.181
-She forgot to give me her number.
ADAM: Argh.

08:36.348 --> 08:38.475
TIMMY: Ah.
-But I know where she works.

08:38.643 --> 08:41.812
Sir, I really don't think
calling her is a good idea.

08:42.396 --> 08:43.731
Timmy, heh.

08:43.898 --> 08:47.151
Poor, sweet, fancy, stupid Timmy.

08:47.818 --> 08:48.819
You're jealous.

08:50.738 --> 08:52.072
Why in the world
would I be jealous?

08:52.239 --> 08:55.034
Because I have this great relationship
and you just got dumped...

08:55.200 --> 08:58.495
...by that squeaky garden rake
from Accounting.

08:58.663 --> 09:00.623
She didn't dump me.
She moved to Chicago.

09:00.790 --> 09:02.249
We're trying to work things out
long-distance.

09:02.416 --> 09:05.044
I hope you do.
She seems like a sweetheart.

09:05.753 --> 09:07.379
Hey, let him call her.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.799
Let him get a taste
of his own sleazy medicine...

09:09.965 --> 09:12.342
...like he gives every girl he blows off.
It makes me sick.

09:12.509 --> 09:13.761
RUSSELL:
Hm.

09:13.928 --> 09:16.430
See, Audrey thinks I should call.

09:18.766 --> 09:22.186
My, you really only hear
what you want to hear.

09:22.352 --> 09:24.772
Thanks. I've been working out.

09:27.107 --> 09:29.193
Hey, is Heather there?

09:29.359 --> 09:32.279
-This is so exciting.
RUSSELL: Heather, it's Russell.

09:33.280 --> 09:36.158
Yeah, hey, I was just thinking
this week we could, uh....

09:36.533 --> 09:39.912
Uh, what's that? Really?

09:40.830 --> 09:43.916
Well, yeah,
you should be there for her.

09:44.208 --> 09:47.336
Sure, well, give me a call
when you get back. Okay.

09:48.588 --> 09:51.006
Shows what you know.
She was just about to call me...

09:51.173 --> 09:54.509
...but she had to rush off
to visit her sick aunt in Nova Scotia.

09:55.219 --> 09:56.971
Oh.

09:57.137 --> 10:01.225
Man, you are having the worst luck
with her. It's crazy.

10:01.851 --> 10:03.644
Really? Just bad luck?

10:03.811 --> 10:06.396
You see no subtext
in Heather's conveyance?

10:06.563 --> 10:08.983
I don't see subtext in anything.

10:09.441 --> 10:11.568
This is like
a classic romantic comedy.

10:11.736 --> 10:13.738
-It sure feels that way.
ADAM: Yes, yes.

10:13.904 --> 10:17.532
All you have to do is get over
some of these obstacles
and you guys can be together.

10:17.700 --> 10:19.785
-It'll be perfect.
-It's gonna be amazing.

10:19.952 --> 10:21.996
Here you go.
Look who stepped up for his wife.

10:22.162 --> 10:25.082
Whoa, everyone in your office
made a pledge.

10:25.249 --> 10:29.837
Oh, and look, there's even one
from Holden McGroin.

10:35.676 --> 10:38.595
Yeah, that was me. Hilarious.

10:38.763 --> 10:39.972
[ALL CHUCKLE]

10:40.139 --> 10:42.892
Well, that's great. And you didn't think
they were generous.

10:43.058 --> 10:45.602
All of them came through.
Thank them for me.

10:45.770 --> 10:48.188
Well, except for Holden McGroin.

10:48.355 --> 10:51.441
-He went away for the weekend with--
-I know. His wife, Pat.

10:51.608 --> 10:53.027
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

10:54.028 --> 10:55.905
-Pat McGroin, heh.
-Pat McGroin.

10:56.739 --> 10:58.448
How'd you get all those people
to pledge?

10:58.615 --> 11:00.492
Did you apologize
for your big speech?

11:00.660 --> 11:03.537
No, I just signed
everybody up myself.

11:04.789 --> 11:06.373
Well, what happens
when it's time to collect?

11:06.540 --> 11:08.292
I'll just pay the 150 bucks myself.

11:08.458 --> 11:09.501
[TIMMY CLEARS THROAT]

11:09.669 --> 11:13.798
-Um, Mr. Bingham?
-Yes, guy who looks like a math TA...

11:13.964 --> 11:15.966
...at every college ever.

11:17.927 --> 11:20.888
These pledges are per kilometer...

11:21.055 --> 11:23.974
...which means that when
Mrs. Bingham completes her 10K...

11:24.141 --> 11:26.811
-...you'll, in fact, owe $1500.
-Ooh.

11:26.977 --> 11:28.145
[WHISTLES]

11:29.146 --> 11:31.816
Guess it's not surprising
how fast I calculated that.

11:34.068 --> 11:36.445
I'll take care of this.
This is a man's work.

11:37.154 --> 11:40.908
Gotta get the old Jaws of Life
to pry open that checkbook of yours.

11:41.075 --> 11:43.994
Unless Audrey never
makes it to the race.

11:44.161 --> 11:46.080
Ah.

11:47.748 --> 11:50.209
I think Jeff's gonna kill Audrey.

11:52.294 --> 11:54.296
[♪♪♪]

11:56.841 --> 11:58.843
[♪♪♪]

12:00.469 --> 12:02.930
Hey, Timmy, I want you
to make reservations for me...

12:03.097 --> 12:06.892
...at a romantic restaurant every night
for the next several weeks.

12:08.310 --> 12:10.062
Oh, I'm so glad to see
that you and Mr. Rhodes...

12:10.229 --> 12:12.147
...are taking it to the next level.

12:13.023 --> 12:15.609
It's not for us. I want to be ready
for when Heather comes back.

12:15.776 --> 12:19.654
Oh, you know what? Let's make it
a Nova Scotian restaurant.

12:21.281 --> 12:23.450
Sir, you're making a big mistake.

12:24.368 --> 12:26.871
Uh, he might be right.

12:27.037 --> 12:30.457
After being up there, Nova Scotian
cuisine may be the last thing she wants.

12:30.624 --> 12:32.918
-Ah, good call. Smart.
-Thank you, thank you.

12:33.085 --> 12:35.379
All right, let's just take
a step back, shall we?

12:35.545 --> 12:37.547
You just called Mr. Rhodes smart.

12:38.632 --> 12:40.885
That's not a red flag that
your judgment might be impaired?

12:41.051 --> 12:43.053
Listen, I'm on Team Adam here.

12:43.220 --> 12:45.890
I think Heather and I were made
for each other.

12:46.056 --> 12:48.058
Okay, look, I was hoping
you would come to your senses...

12:48.225 --> 12:50.310
...but you leave me no choice.

12:52.729 --> 12:54.231
Heather's Facebook page.

12:54.398 --> 12:57.109
Her profile says
she's in a relationship...

12:57.276 --> 12:59.945
...and her status says she's at
this New York City restaurant...

13:00.112 --> 13:02.614
...with this very handsome man
at this very moment.

13:02.781 --> 13:04.574
[RUSSELL SIGHS]

13:05.659 --> 13:07.619
Do you know what this means?

13:09.454 --> 13:10.831
I do.

13:10.998 --> 13:12.791
-She's back in town, dude.
-Heh, heh.

13:14.459 --> 13:17.379
And she's at McSweeney's
with one of her gay buddies.

13:17.546 --> 13:20.674
And she's listed us
as being in a relationship.

13:20.841 --> 13:23.552
-All right, I'm gonna go surprise her.
-That is a great idea.

13:23.718 --> 13:25.762
-Come with me.
-I'm coming.

13:32.727 --> 13:34.980
AUDREY: Hey, Jeff,
I need to get up early for the fun run.

13:35.147 --> 13:39.234
-Can you set the alarm for 6:15?
-Already did.

13:41.195 --> 13:44.614
Hey, you know what you got to do
before a big race?

13:44.781 --> 13:47.159
-Hydrate.
-Heh, good idea.

13:47.993 --> 13:49.328
Finish it.

13:51.330 --> 13:52.539
Thattagirl.

13:52.706 --> 13:54.374
[AUDREY CHUCKLES]

13:57.962 --> 14:02.507
You know,
just to be on the safe side...

14:02.674 --> 14:04.593
...I'm gonna take one of these.

14:07.054 --> 14:10.349
-Take one of what?
-Your sleeping pills.

14:12.601 --> 14:16.271
-Oh, I.... I wouldn't.
-I already did.

14:17.147 --> 14:19.233
Oh.

14:19.691 --> 14:22.569
This way, I'll be good
and rested for the race.

14:22.736 --> 14:24.404
See you tomorrow.

14:26.073 --> 14:27.741
Or the next day.

14:30.035 --> 14:32.037
[♪♪♪]

14:33.163 --> 14:35.165
[CHATTERING]

14:38.627 --> 14:40.712
Sir, stop.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.883
-What are you doing here?
-I can't let you go through with this.

14:45.009 --> 14:47.261
Oh, I know what's going on.

14:47.427 --> 14:49.554
You're worried that
if I get in a serious relationship...

14:49.721 --> 14:52.141
...it's gonna hurt
the friendship we have.

14:53.976 --> 14:55.685
Do you have a backup guess?

14:57.146 --> 14:58.813
I implore you to think back.

14:58.981 --> 15:02.442
Everything Heather has said and done
constitutes a classic blow-off.

15:05.112 --> 15:06.821
Oh, shoot.

15:06.989 --> 15:09.283
I've got to run into the office.

15:09.992 --> 15:12.827
She was just about to call me,
but then she had to suddenly rush up...

15:12.995 --> 15:15.455
...and visit her sick aunt
in Nova Scotia.

15:15.998 --> 15:18.583
Wow, I just called Heather
and a woman who sounds just like her...

15:18.750 --> 15:21.586
...answered and said
she found Heather's phone.

15:21.753 --> 15:23.630
-I'm very sorry, sir.
-Don't feel sorry for me.

15:23.797 --> 15:24.798
Feel sorry for Heather.

15:24.965 --> 15:26.800
She's the one stuck up
in Nova Scotia with no phone.

15:26.967 --> 15:28.593
Argh.

15:28.760 --> 15:30.095
These are all evasive maneuvers...

15:30.262 --> 15:32.222
...that you yourself
have used on women.

15:32.932 --> 15:35.100
Sir, Heather's using the technique
that you refer to as...

15:35.267 --> 15:37.394
...the old hump and dump.

15:40.022 --> 15:41.440
[SIGHS]

15:42.232 --> 15:43.943
I think I've been Russelled.

15:46.195 --> 15:47.404
[RUSSELL GROANS]

15:48.738 --> 15:50.824
You know, on some level,
I think I knew...

15:50.991 --> 15:54.286
...but I liked her so much,
I just didn't want to believe it.

15:54.453 --> 15:56.496
-We've all been there, sir.
-Oh, yeah, you got dumped...

15:56.663 --> 15:59.333
...by that four-eyed javelin
from Accounting.

16:00.209 --> 16:01.876
Anyway, you were right.
I guess I owe you--

16:02.044 --> 16:03.378
HEATHER:
Russell?

16:03.587 --> 16:04.671
[HEATHER LAUGHS]

16:04.838 --> 16:07.007
I'm so glad you're here.

16:07.174 --> 16:09.969
-You are?
-Of course.

16:11.470 --> 16:14.306
-Wow, I thought you were going to--
-Nova Scotia. I was.

16:14.473 --> 16:17.017
But I didn't have to
because my sick aunt got better.

16:17.184 --> 16:19.478
-Oh, well, that's great.
-And I wanted to call you...

16:19.644 --> 16:20.980
...but I lost my phone.

16:21.146 --> 16:24.149
I was so upset, so my friend Gordon
took me out for a drink.

16:24.316 --> 16:25.317
Hi.

16:28.278 --> 16:31.281
-His boyfriend's out of town.
-So it's just us girls.

16:32.616 --> 16:35.785
-How did you know to come here?
-Your Facebook page.

16:35.952 --> 16:39.498
Oh, is it okay I said
we were in a relationship?

16:39.664 --> 16:41.583
Is that dress red?

16:41.750 --> 16:44.253
Look, you two don't need me
chaperoning.

16:44.419 --> 16:47.797
Gordon out. As if it wasn't obvious.

16:48.173 --> 16:49.174
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

16:50.175 --> 16:52.344
Um, all right, I'll come over
in one second, all right?

16:57.766 --> 16:59.184
[SIGHS]

17:02.271 --> 17:04.314
Wow, I guess it's me
who owes you an apology.

17:04.856 --> 17:06.941
Shh, shh, shh.

17:07.942 --> 17:10.112
Timmy, I just hope one day
you won't be so cynical...

17:10.279 --> 17:13.657
...and you can open your heart
to romance.

17:14.658 --> 17:16.576
[RUSSELL WHISTLING]

17:18.328 --> 17:19.829
Hello.

17:19.996 --> 17:22.207
Oh, my gosh.

17:22.374 --> 17:23.875
These are so beautiful.

17:27.879 --> 17:29.506
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

17:29.673 --> 17:31.050
[♪♪♪]

17:31.216 --> 17:32.509
Aud.

17:33.760 --> 17:35.345
Aud.

17:37.681 --> 17:39.974
[AUDREY SNORING]

17:52.904 --> 17:54.323
[GASPS]

18:13.550 --> 18:15.552
[THE KINKS' "SLEEPWALKER"
PLAYING]

18:24.144 --> 18:27.522
♪ Everybody got problems, buddy
I got mine ♪

18:28.273 --> 18:31.901
♪ When midnight comes around
I start to lose my mind ♪

18:32.569 --> 18:37.073
♪ When the sun puts out the light
I join the creatures of the night ♪

18:37.241 --> 18:38.700
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

18:41.411 --> 18:43.037
♪ I'm a sleepwalker ♪

18:45.624 --> 18:47.709
♪ I'm a night stalker ♪

18:50.003 --> 18:52.422
♪ I'm a street walker ♪

18:54.508 --> 18:56.718
♪ I'm a night hawker ♪

18:59.513 --> 19:02.849
♪ Everybody got secrets
That they wanna hide ♪

19:03.808 --> 19:07.229
♪ When midnight comes along
I take a look inside ♪

19:07.687 --> 19:12.151
♪ Don't go talkin' in your sleep
I might come in for a peep ♪

19:12.317 --> 19:14.778
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

19:20.534 --> 19:22.619
♪ I'm a sleepwalker ♪♪

19:26.581 --> 19:27.749
[♪♪♪]

19:28.167 --> 19:29.709
So you slept through the fun run?

19:29.876 --> 19:31.878
Heh, can you believe it?

19:33.880 --> 19:36.049
Right through my alarm.

19:36.425 --> 19:38.635
But I had the weirdest dream
that I did run it.

19:38.802 --> 19:40.011
It was so real.

19:40.179 --> 19:42.806
But not real enough to collect money
from my coworkers.

19:43.640 --> 19:46.643
Well, anyways, the gang
at the office will be bummed.

19:46.810 --> 19:50.189
-They live to give.
-Oh, heh, heh.

19:50.355 --> 19:53.733
Well, tell them not to worry. I wrote
a check to cover all their pledges.

19:53.900 --> 19:55.694
-Did you, now?
-Yeah.

19:55.860 --> 19:58.863
For, uh, all 1500?

19:59.239 --> 20:02.116
Yeah. Just because I overslept,
the charity shouldn't suffer.

20:02.284 --> 20:03.452
I'm gonna go mail this.

20:06.079 --> 20:09.583
You're silently resenting her
right now, aren't you?

20:11.668 --> 20:12.877
I am.

20:13.086 --> 20:15.088
[♪♪♪]

20:17.299 --> 20:18.342
[♪♪♪]

20:18.508 --> 20:19.926
[SIGHS]

20:20.844 --> 20:23.179
Good morning, Heather.

20:23.347 --> 20:26.308
I have a feeling that every morning
with you will be a good one.

20:31.145 --> 20:32.564
[GRUNTS]

20:35.817 --> 20:38.528
HEATHER:
Russell, sorry I had to sneak out...

20:38.695 --> 20:42.824
...but my National Guard unit
was called into duty this morning.

20:44.200 --> 20:46.703
I can't tell you where I'll be
or when I'll be back...

20:46.870 --> 20:49.664
...but I'll give you a call
when I return.

21:03.011 --> 21:05.013
[♪♪♪]

21:09.518 --> 21:11.520
[♪♪♪]
